<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 19.5px; font-weight: bold;">For more information or to book our Twin Centre Holidays &amp; Tours please call 01483 79 11 11</p>
<p>Discover magnificent landscapes, dramatic scenery, and the varied flora &amp; fauna and wildlife of the Julian Alps. The majestic backdrops are formed by the jagged summits of Mount Triglav, Slovenia’s highest mountain (2,864m) and namesake of the country’s National Park which covers 880 sq. km. Nestled in this picturesque area are the intriguing destinations of <a data-udi="umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e}" title="Lake Bled">Lake Bled</a>, Lake Bohinj, Kranjska Gora and Bovec: Lake Bled’s beauty is renowned, nestled amidst dense pine forests and surrounded by the dramatic snow-capped Julian Alps, and its famous tiny wooded island has become the national symbol of Slovenia. Fairy-tale <a data-udi="umb://document/b56bdaf2399f46828fa1f01256cae753" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b56bdaf2399f46828fa1f01256cae753}" title="Lake Bohinj">Lake Bohinj</a> enjoys one of the most picturesque and unspoilt natural settings at the foot of Mt Vogel. The small picturesque village of Kranjska Gora sits at the confluence of the Sava Dolinka and Pišnica valleys against the dramatic backdrop of the Julian Alps. <a data-udi="umb://document/7cc8e45320754ead8a9f026b9de3f1ad" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7cc8e45320754ead8a9f026b9de3f1ad}" title="Bovec">Bovec</a> offers a fantastic array of activities in its idyllic valley which also was the setting for many scenes from the ‘Chronicles of Narnia’ film.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>Days 1 to 3 Lake Bohinj:</strong><br />Following your arrival at Ljubljana airport on a Sunday you will be transferred to your resort and <a data-udi="umb://document/2aeb8216bf2947b9951b9a65f072cf51" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2aeb8216bf2947b9951b9a65f072cf51}" title="Hotel Jezero">Hotel Jezero</a> in Lake Bohinj for your 3 nights stay on half board (buffet breakfast and dinner with free wine, beer and soft drinks with dinner). <strong>Day 2</strong>, we will join the Julian Alps excursion to enjoy the marvellous mountain scenery of the neighbouring Alpine mountains range for the day and passport is a requirement. <strong>Day 3</strong> at leisure to enjoy the beautiful Lake Bohinj. <strong>Day 4:</strong> Wednesday transfer to Bovec by train from Bohinj.</p>
<p><strong>Days 4 to 6, Bovec:</strong> <br />Arrive Bovec early afternoon for your 3-night stay at the Hotel Alp a 3-star hotel on half board (buffet breakfast and dinner) and enjoy an afternoon to relax and enjoy the high street with its cafés and few shops. <strong>Day 5:</strong> Join the local tourist board excursion (payable locally) to the majestic Boka waterfall or another local excursion. <strong>Day 6:</strong> to enjoy the local beautiful walks and hikes and water activities on River Soča. <strong>Day 7:</strong> Saturday transfer to <a data-udi="umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab}" title="Kranjska Gora">Kranjska Gora</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Days 7 to 11, Kranjska Gora:</strong> arrive early afternoon for your 4-night stay at <a data-udi="umb://document/b27591e078194ddd981ff8e811b26cba" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b27591e078194ddd981ff8e811b26cba}" title="Hotel Kompas">Hotel Kompas</a> on half board (buffet breakfast and dinner) Enjoy the small village of Kranjska Gora with a coffee or beer or two surrounded with a superb view of the peaks of the beautiful mountains. <strong>Day 8</strong> at leisure to enjoy the resort and local walks to Lake Jasna and or Zelenci nature reserve and many local hikes or walks to enjoy at your leisure. <strong>Day 9:</strong> Join our local taste of Slovenia excursion for full day of following river Soča by train, boat and coach and finishing at the largest wine cellar in Slovenia for some wine tasting and perhaps bring some back in the suitcase. <strong>Day 10:</strong> Chose from one of the many possible walks towards the mountains or walk to the village of Podkoren or Mojstrana.</p>
Flights are from Gatwick and Stansted to Ljubljana with EasyJet departing Sundays and return Wednesday, includes all transfers and services of local reps. Holiday code: SIXX 3001.</div>
